Description: Shell of a marine gastropod mollusc of the Mediterranean 'Nassa gibbosula' species.
Curator's comments: Found in box of unregistered shells with other shells that had handwritten slips written by Petrie identifying the shell species and naming Naukratis as the provenance. This shell was found with a note by Petrie: 'Nassa gibbosula Medit.'. Note Nassa gibbosula not in World Register of Marine Species.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (WC.28)
